.TH "mcp_reg_write" 9 "mcp_reg_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mcp_reg_write \- write a device register
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" mcp_reg_write
.BI "(struct mcp *mcp "  ","
.BI "unsigned int reg "  ","
.BI "unsigned int val "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mcp" 12
MCP interface structure
.IP "reg" 12
4-bit register index
.IP "val" 12
16-bit data value

Write a device register.  The MCP interface must be enabled
to prevent this function hanging.
